# Cross-Platform (Windows + Mac)

All code changes must work on **Windows** and **Mac**.

## Paths

- Use `path.join()` / `resolve()` from `path`; avoid hardcoded `/` or `\`.
- Use `process.platform === "win32"` when behavior must differ; keep the other platform in mind.

## Shell / Process

- **utils/shell.ts**: Prefer `spawnSync` with explicit args; use `shell: true` only when necessary (e.g. to resolve npm global `.cmd`). On Windows, long arguments must not be split by the shell—prefer resolving the executable path and spawning without shell when passing long prompts.
- Use `resolveCommandPath(cmd)` so the real executable (e.g. `codex.cmd` on Windows) is used; prefer `.cmd` on Windows when `where` returns multiple entries.
- Test both: PowerShell (Windows) and bash/zsh (Mac).

## Scripts (templates)

- `*.sh`: Use POSIX-compatible commands and no bash-only features if the script may run on Windows (e.g. via Git Bash or WSL). Prefer `planforge` CLI so logic stays in Node and works everywhere.

## Checklist

- [ ] No Windows-only or Mac-only assumptions (paths, line endings, shell quoting).
- [ ] If you add a platform branch, the other platform path is implemented and tested in mind.
